application   choupoSolve;
description   "Antisolvent + COOLING crystallisation of NaCl: the same drowning-out brine + ethanol as crystalliser06, but the crystalliser is COOLED to 5 C. The eNRTL is now temperature-dependent (tau(T)=tau_25*298.15/T, A_DH(T) via eps_w(T)/rho_w(T), Born at T) and Ksp(T) shifts by van't Hoff with NaCl's enthalpy of solution -- so cooling adds to the antisolvent's effect (yield 61% -> 70%). Exercises the T-dependent electrolyte path.";
verbosity     3;
